  schema:name "Why Universalist Coordination Breaks" ;
  schema:description "How four commitments shared by mutualist and liberal organizing — teleology, epistemic universalism, proceduralism, and cooperative reciprocity — form a chain that collapses under the conditions it claims to address." ;
